Exercise 4

How many points do the Courage typically win by (on average)? Use the example code below to get started. You‚Äôll encounter a new function: abs() is the absolute value function. It takes the absolute value of a number. Why do we want to use this absolute value function here?

Hint: We are only interested in games the Courage wins, therefore we should filter() for those games first.

courage |&gt;
  filter(___) |&gt;
  mutate(win_pts = abs(home_pts - away_pts)) |&gt;
  summarize(___)

Exercise 5

How many points do NC Courage score when they win (on average)? Note this is different than how many points they ‚Äúwin by‚Äù. How many points do the Courage score when they lose on average?

To calculate this we first need to determine how many points NC Courage scored in every game. We can use if_else() logic again to find this value for each game, and store it in a new column, courage_pts.

courage &lt;- courage |&gt;
  mutate(courage_pts = if_else(home_team == "NC", home_pts, away_pts))

